Answer (numerical number):
gpt_response:
The molecular weight of 1-(3-aminocyclobutyl)oxy-3-ethoxypropan-2-ol can be calculated by adding up the atomic weights of all the elements present in the compound.

1- (Cyclobutyl)oxy-3- ethoxypropan-2-ol consists of the following elements and their corresponding atomic weights:
- Carbon (C): 4 atoms x 12.01 g/mol = 48.04 g/mol
- Hydrogen (H): 10 atoms x 1.01 g/mol = 10.10 g/mol
- Oxygen (O): 3 atoms x 16.00 g/mol = 48.00 g/mol
- Nitrogen (N): 1 atom x 14.01 g/mol = 14.01 g/mol

Adding up these values gives:
48.04 g/mol + 10.10 g/mol + 48.00 g/mol + 14.01 g/mol = 120.15 g/mol

Therefore, the molecular weight of 1-(3-aminocyclobutyl)oxy-3-ethoxypropan-2-ol is 120.15 g/mol.
